1
00:00:06,942 --> 00:00:11,025
(tense eerie instrumental music)

2
00:00:43,036 --> 00:00:46,189
- [Narrator] Our minds
are never repressed.

3
00:00:46,239 --> 00:00:50,505
Our thoughts tumble between
the light and the darkness.

4
00:00:50,555 --> 00:00:54,722
We have always preferred the
light and avoided the dark.

5
00:00:55,654 --> 00:00:59,737
(tense eerie instrumental music)

6
00:01:14,839 --> 00:01:17,915
- Something strange has been happening.

7
00:01:17,965 --> 00:01:18,882
This voice,

8
00:01:21,289 --> 00:01:24,035
I just can't get rid of this feeling.

9
00:01:24,085 --> 00:01:26,585
(tense music)

10
00:01:28,257 --> 00:01:29,174
I'm afraid.

11
00:01:30,518 --> 00:01:31,652
I'm afraid.

12
00:01:31,702 --> 00:01:34,202
(tense music)

13
00:01:38,855 --> 00:01:41,467
Now, this is exactly what
I've been talking about, Phil.

14
00:01:41,517 --> 00:01:43,260
I'm not some kind of a cirus act.

15
00:01:43,310 --> 00:01:44,656
- I know, I know, I'm sorry.

16
00:01:44,706 --> 00:01:47,335
- Yeah, people must let me
explain the scientific aspect

17
00:01:47,385 --> 00:01:49,290
of what a gift like mine can mean,

18
00:01:49,340 --> 00:01:50,901
the hundreds I can help.

19
00:01:50,951 --> 00:01:52,072
- All right, I'll take care of it.

20
00:01:52,122 --> 00:01:53,733
I'll have the mind reading
part removed immediately,

21
00:01:53,783 --> 00:01:54,566
all right?

22
00:01:54,616 --> 00:01:55,733
Don't worry about it.

23
00:01:55,783 --> 00:01:57,340
- Okay.

24
00:01:57,390 --> 00:01:59,890
(tense music)

25
00:02:01,154 --> 00:02:03,987
(soft chattering)

26
00:02:08,409 --> 00:02:11,852
- [Eerie Voice] Come to me, Gail.

27
00:02:11,902 --> 00:02:14,606
- Ah, Dr. Peyton, you were very amusing.

28
00:02:14,656 --> 00:02:16,363
May I have your autograph, please?

29
00:02:16,413 --> 00:02:19,330
- Your time is up.
- Your autograph?

30
00:02:20,732 --> 00:02:23,369
- [Eerie Voice] I want you to die.

31
00:02:23,419 --> 00:02:25,761
- I'm sorry, but I must
insist that it's over today.

32
00:02:25,811 --> 00:02:26,644
I'm sorry.

33
00:02:29,680 --> 00:02:31,013
- [Man] Strange.

34
00:02:32,886 --> 00:02:35,386
(eerie music)

35
00:02:42,810 --> 00:02:44,715
- Something strange has been happening.

36
00:02:44,765 --> 00:02:48,932
I don't know, it's just never
happened like this before.

37
00:02:51,554 --> 00:02:53,471
I'm receiving thoughts.

38
00:02:55,250 --> 00:02:57,333
It's like I hear a voice,

39
00:02:58,874 --> 00:03:01,020
and it's so cold,

40
00:03:01,070 --> 00:03:03,820
and I know it doesn't make sense,

41
00:03:05,364 --> 00:03:07,114
but I feel it's evil.

42
00:03:11,286 --> 00:03:13,033
I, I don't know, maybe, uh,

43
00:03:13,083 --> 00:03:14,904
maybe it's because I'm
against this whole damn tour.

44
00:03:14,954 --> 00:03:19,121
I just wish Phil hadn't
been so insistent about it.

45
00:03:21,999 --> 00:03:23,249
But this voice,

46
00:03:25,369 --> 00:03:28,452
I just can't get rid of this feeling.

47
00:03:32,239 --> 00:03:33,156
I'm afraid.

48
00:03:36,748 --> 00:03:38,691
I'm afraid that.

49
00:03:38,741 --> 00:03:39,687
(clicks)

50
00:03:39,737 --> 00:03:42,237
(tense music)

51
00:03:43,728 --> 00:03:46,645
(upbeat pop music)

52
00:04:09,874 --> 00:04:10,707
- Gail,

53
00:04:11,645 --> 00:04:13,463
you're so excitable sometimes.

54
00:04:13,513 --> 00:04:14,882
Try to see this professionally.

55
00:04:14,932 --> 00:04:16,642
It takes time to build a career.

56
00:04:16,692 --> 00:04:19,147
- A career in what, a freak in a sideshow?

57
00:04:19,197 --> 00:04:21,278
- I have not forgotten any
of the scientific aspect,

58
00:04:21,328 --> 00:04:23,748
but first we have to build the awareness.

59
00:04:23,798 --> 00:04:24,581
- Awareness?

60
00:04:24,631 --> 00:04:26,540
Phil, I'm a psychologist,
I wanna help people.

61
00:04:26,590 --> 00:04:29,026
- You will help people,
Gail, more than you think.

62
00:04:29,076 --> 00:04:30,916
Trust me, okay?

63
00:04:30,966 --> 00:04:32,039
- I do, but--

64
00:04:32,089 --> 00:04:34,634
- Hey, hey, hey, hey, read my mind.

65
00:04:34,684 --> 00:04:37,585
Nothing but good things in
store for you, lady, okay?

66
00:04:37,635 --> 00:04:38,983
Now, come on, back to business.

67
00:04:39,033 --> 00:04:40,785
- Oh, boy, you never stop working, do you?

68
00:04:40,835 --> 00:04:42,518
- What, just doing my job.

69
00:04:42,568 --> 00:04:45,335
45 minutes to press time, remember?

70
00:04:45,385 --> 00:04:47,885
(tense music)

71
00:04:53,573 --> 00:04:55,859
Now, just remember, keep
your answers short and sweet.

72
00:04:55,909 --> 00:04:57,889
Don't get into any debates
about the meaning of life,

73
00:04:57,939 --> 00:05:00,382
and don't go jabbering
on about nothing at all.

74
00:05:00,432 --> 00:05:03,212
Just remember, you are
promoting yourself, right?

75
00:05:03,262 --> 00:05:04,045
- Right.

76
00:05:04,095 --> 00:05:04,878
- Good.

77
00:05:04,928 --> 00:05:06,420
Now you get out there
and knock 'em dead, kid.

78
00:05:06,470 --> 00:05:07,253
Come on.

79
00:05:07,303 --> 00:05:09,553
(clapping)

80
00:05:15,601 --> 00:05:16,793
- Good day to you all.

81
00:05:16,843 --> 00:05:18,143
I'm Dr. Gail Peyton.

82
00:05:18,193 --> 00:05:19,896
I'm ready for your questions.

83
00:05:19,946 --> 00:05:20,729
Uh, yes?

84
00:05:20,779 --> 00:05:23,646
- [Woman In Red] Dr. Peyton,
your book discusses your gift

85
00:05:23,696 --> 00:05:26,083
of reading minds in
relation to helping patients

86
00:05:26,133 --> 00:05:27,839
in psychoanalysis.

87
00:05:27,889 --> 00:05:31,121
If that is true, do
you think it's ethical?

88
00:05:31,171 --> 00:05:33,246
- I don't think it's like
wiretapping their minds,

89
00:05:33,296 --> 00:05:35,307
if that's what you're getting at.

90
00:05:35,357 --> 00:05:38,027
You really shouldn't call it mind reading.

91
00:05:38,077 --> 00:05:41,230
I mean, if anything it's
more like mind listening.

92
00:05:41,280 --> 00:05:43,923
People who come to me want and need help.

93
00:05:43,973 --> 00:05:46,956
The gift I have enables
me to cure them faster.

94
00:05:47,006 --> 00:05:48,238
Yes?

95
00:05:48,288 --> 00:05:50,526
- Yeah, I attended your
seminar this afternoon.

96
00:05:50,576 --> 00:05:54,608
Isn't this just an elaborate parlor trick?

97
00:05:54,658 --> 00:05:57,648
- I sometimes have wished
it was some kind of trick,

98
00:05:57,698 --> 00:05:59,447
but I'm afraid not.

99
00:05:59,497 --> 00:06:01,391
I live with this,

100
00:06:01,441 --> 00:06:03,500
especially in my childhood
when I had to learn

101
00:06:03,550 --> 00:06:04,906
how to control it.

102
00:06:04,956 --> 00:06:06,393
- Ah, come on, Dr. Peyton,

103
00:06:06,443 --> 00:06:08,970
you really expect us to fall for this?

104
00:06:09,020 --> 00:06:11,228
Come on, lady, give me a break.

105
00:06:11,278 --> 00:06:12,676
- No, this lady won't give you a break.

106
00:06:12,726 --> 00:06:14,861
You sure haven't given me one.

107
00:06:14,911 --> 00:06:16,081
- [Man Voiceover] That's impossible.

108
00:06:16,131 --> 00:06:17,687
She couldn't have read my mind.

109
00:06:17,737 --> 00:06:19,733
- Oh, and what is so impossible?

110
00:06:19,783 --> 00:06:22,033
- Oh my God, she can do it.

111
00:06:23,362 --> 00:06:25,612
(chuckles)

112
00:06:27,475 --> 00:06:29,722
- Dr. Peyton, you've started a new book.

113
00:06:29,772 --> 00:06:31,403
Could you tell us a little bit about it?

114
00:06:31,453 --> 00:06:32,823
- Uh, no, I'm not--

115
00:06:32,873 --> 00:06:35,068
- Yes, yes, she has.

116
00:06:35,118 --> 00:06:36,802
Uh, I was out to LA recently.

117
00:06:36,852 --> 00:06:39,457
Believe me, the Hollywood
minds are intriguing.

118
00:06:39,507 --> 00:06:43,674
Let me tell you, no, no, you'd
better wait for the book.

119
00:06:45,939 --> 00:06:48,106
- Well, now that you know.

120
00:06:50,672 --> 00:06:53,770
- [Eerie Voice] Time to pay.

121
00:06:53,820 --> 00:06:55,893
(tense music)

122
00:06:55,943 --> 00:06:57,443
I want you to die.

123
00:06:59,642 --> 00:07:00,559
Come to me.

124
00:07:02,695 --> 00:07:04,764
(gasps)

125
00:07:04,814 --> 00:07:05,668
- Are you all right?

126
00:07:05,718 --> 00:07:08,412
- Oh, the voice, the voice was back.

127
00:07:08,462 --> 00:07:09,919
- No, it's okay, it's okay.

128
00:07:09,969 --> 00:07:11,091
Everything's gonna be all right.

129
00:07:11,141 --> 00:07:12,189
- He wants to kill me.

130
00:07:12,239 --> 00:07:13,237
- Who wants to kill you?

131
00:07:13,287 --> 00:07:15,339
- No, no, it's all right,
it's just a slight trauma.

132
00:07:15,389 --> 00:07:17,748
It's inherent to mind reading.

133
00:07:17,798 --> 00:07:19,334
- I, I'm sorry.

134
00:07:19,384 --> 00:07:20,501
- It's okay, honey.

135
00:07:20,551 --> 00:07:22,459
Mind reading takes up a lot of energy.

136
00:07:22,509 --> 00:07:25,264
Uh, come on, honey, I'll
take care of ya, don't worry.

137
00:07:25,314 --> 00:07:27,672
I'm sorry, but that's gonna
have to be all for today.

138
00:07:27,722 --> 00:07:28,555
Come on.

139
00:07:29,692 --> 00:07:32,859
- Is this some kind of trick, or what?

140
00:07:39,806 --> 00:07:42,306
(tense music)

141
00:07:45,562 --> 00:07:48,540
- [Phil] Gail, I am glad
to see you lookin' better.

142
00:07:48,590 --> 00:07:50,340
- Oh, I'm okay, Phil.

143
00:07:51,370 --> 00:07:52,980
That voice.

144
00:07:53,030 --> 00:07:54,510
- Oh, come on, Gail.

145
00:07:54,560 --> 00:07:56,870
- No, I heard it in
the lobby this morning.

146
00:07:56,920 --> 00:07:58,044
- Look, don't panic.

147
00:07:58,094 --> 00:07:59,801
You're famous now, you're gonna be a star.

148
00:07:59,851 --> 00:08:02,707
- I don't wanna be a star, you know that.

149
00:08:02,757 --> 00:08:05,152
- Look, I've got great
things coming up for you.

150
00:08:05,202 --> 00:08:05,985
Believe me.

151
00:08:06,035 --> 00:08:07,275
This is good.

152
00:08:07,325 --> 00:08:10,408
(soft radio chatter)

153
00:08:11,796 --> 00:08:15,129
(upbeat rhythmic music)

154
00:08:22,482 --> 00:08:24,232
- I'll be right back.

155
00:08:28,428 --> 00:08:29,601
Can I get you anything else?

156
00:08:29,651 --> 00:08:30,847
- [Phil] Where's the phone, please?

157
00:08:30,897 --> 00:08:31,883
- Over on the bar.

158
00:08:31,933 --> 00:08:33,218
- Thank you.

159
00:08:33,268 --> 00:08:34,973
- And, uh, what about you, ma'am?

160
00:08:35,023 --> 00:08:36,917
- I'll have another mineral water, please.

161
00:08:36,967 --> 00:08:39,258
- Why don't you find
yourself a water fountain?

162
00:08:39,308 --> 00:08:41,154
Uh, anything else?

163
00:08:41,204 --> 00:08:42,444
- Yes, two lemons.

164
00:08:42,494 --> 00:08:45,783
One lemon for me and put the
other one in a water fountain.

165
00:08:45,833 --> 00:08:46,666
- Sure.

166
00:08:48,960 --> 00:08:52,293
(upbeat rhythmic music)

167
00:09:09,174 --> 00:09:11,733
- You are going to be very big, lady.

168
00:09:11,783 --> 00:09:13,962
You'll never guess who I just rang up.

169
00:09:14,012 --> 00:09:15,065
- Donahue, too.

170
00:09:15,115 --> 00:09:18,046
- Yeah, Geraldo and
Donahue, can ya believe it?

171
00:09:18,096 --> 00:09:19,629
I got you booked on both shows.

172
00:09:19,679 --> 00:09:22,252
It's gonna be barrels of
money, barrels of money.

173
00:09:22,302 --> 00:09:23,692
Donahue's people want you next week,

174
00:09:23,742 --> 00:09:26,224
and I squeezed in Geraldo
while we're at the convention.

175
00:09:26,274 --> 00:09:29,040
Hey, hey, hey, hey, come back here.

176
00:09:29,090 --> 00:09:31,098
I've got a reporter from the
Times coming here tomorrow

177
00:09:31,148 --> 00:09:32,156
at 10 o'clock.

178
00:09:32,206 --> 00:09:34,393
It's big money, honey,
buy anything you want.

179
00:09:34,443 --> 00:09:35,995
Come one, I'm a genius, aint' I?

180
00:09:36,045 --> 00:09:36,828
- No.
- No?

181
00:09:36,878 --> 00:09:38,645
- But I still like you.

182
00:09:38,695 --> 00:09:41,339
Look, I'm sorry, Phil, but you know.

183
00:09:41,389 --> 00:09:44,845
- I know, yeah, I'll get
ya some patients, too.

184
00:09:44,895 --> 00:09:46,274
- I sure hope so.

185
00:09:46,324 --> 00:09:47,796
- Come on, we got a lot to celebrate.

186
00:09:47,846 --> 00:09:52,013
Hey, Tony, come on, a barrel
of your best champagne.

187
00:09:53,519 --> 00:09:56,436
(slow tense music)

188
00:10:47,248 --> 00:10:49,006
(sighs)

189
00:10:49,056 --> 00:10:51,556
(tense music)

190
00:10:58,369 --> 00:11:00,586
- [Eerie Voice] Gail.

191
00:11:00,636 --> 00:11:01,469
I'm here.

192
00:11:04,139 --> 00:11:06,639
(tense music)

193
00:11:07,571 --> 00:11:09,238
No one can save you.

194
00:11:10,725 --> 00:11:12,559
(tense music)

195
00:11:12,609 --> 00:11:14,763
(elevator dings)

196
00:11:14,813 --> 00:11:17,313
(tense music)

197
00:11:25,628 --> 00:11:28,961
- Oh, uh, any messages for 1503, please?

198
00:11:30,114 --> 00:11:30,947
Thank you.

199
00:11:33,713 --> 00:11:35,230
- [Eerie Voice] Gail,

200
00:11:35,280 --> 00:11:36,863
you can't get away.

201
00:11:39,381 --> 00:11:41,714
- Oh, uh, where's the house phone, please?

202
00:11:41,764 --> 00:11:42,597
Thank you.

203
00:11:43,484 --> 00:11:45,984
(tense music)

204
00:11:47,747 --> 00:11:49,164
Uh, 1504, please.

205
00:11:50,620 --> 00:11:52,537
Come on, Phil, pick up.

206
00:11:53,664 --> 00:11:56,825
- [Eerie Voice] I want you to die

207
00:11:56,875 --> 00:11:58,375
slow and painful.

208
00:11:59,973 --> 00:12:00,806
- Oh, oh!

209
00:12:03,045 --> 00:12:03,878
Oh.

210
00:12:04,736 --> 00:12:05,848
- Are you all right, ma'am?

211
00:12:05,898 --> 00:12:08,828
- That man, did, did you see him?

212
00:12:08,878 --> 00:12:10,593
- Are you sure you're okay?

213
00:12:10,643 --> 00:12:12,810
(gasping)

214
00:12:16,451 --> 00:12:18,721
- Oh, you, you, you've got to help me.

215
00:12:18,771 --> 00:12:21,340
Someone is trying to kill me.

216
00:12:21,390 --> 00:12:23,401
- Calm down, Miss, calm down.

217
00:12:23,451 --> 00:12:24,964
- Stop him, please.

218
00:12:25,014 --> 00:12:26,458
- Who, who is it?

219
00:12:26,508 --> 00:12:29,096
- He's here, he's in the hotel.

220
00:12:29,146 --> 00:12:30,910
I heard him.

221
00:12:30,960 --> 00:12:32,358
He's following me.

222
00:12:32,408 --> 00:12:34,375
- Okay, show me the man, lady.

223
00:12:34,425 --> 00:12:37,731
- Hey, hey, hey, this
lady is the mind reader.

224
00:12:37,781 --> 00:12:40,626
- Ah, is this a publicity thing, ma'am.

225
00:12:40,676 --> 00:12:42,842
- No, for God's sake, it's true.

226
00:12:42,892 --> 00:12:44,225
I read his mind.

227
00:12:45,452 --> 00:12:47,070
You've got to believe me.

228
00:12:47,120 --> 00:12:51,332
- (chuckles) Right, I believe you.

229
00:12:51,382 --> 00:12:55,159
I'm going to arrest someone
because you read his mind.

230
00:12:55,209 --> 00:12:58,623
Look, lady, go find someone
else for your publicity stunt.

231
00:12:58,673 --> 00:13:00,336
- No.
- And don't bother me.

232
00:13:00,386 --> 00:13:01,696
Come on.
- No.

233
00:13:01,746 --> 00:13:04,349
- [Eerie Voice] Come to me, Gail.

234
00:13:04,399 --> 00:13:05,431
- No.

235
00:13:05,481 --> 00:13:07,231
- Die.
- No, stop it!

236
00:13:08,172 --> 00:13:11,962
Oh, please help me, he's here, I know it!

237
00:13:12,012 --> 00:13:14,110
- Lady, stop playing games.

238
00:13:14,160 --> 00:13:16,228
- I'm not playing games.

239
00:13:16,278 --> 00:13:17,276
Help me.

240
00:13:17,326 --> 00:13:19,920
- Look, lady, come on, I'm
gonna take you to your room.

241
00:13:19,970 --> 00:13:21,541
- No, no.
- Come on.

242
00:13:21,591 --> 00:13:22,974
- No, no.
- Come on.

243
00:13:23,024 --> 00:13:25,243
- Phil, Phil, Phil, I
heard the voice again.

244
00:13:25,293 --> 00:13:26,470
- It's, it's all right.
- They don't believe me.

245
00:13:26,520 --> 00:13:27,323
They don't.
- It's all right.

246
00:13:27,373 --> 00:13:28,897
- You do, don't you, Phil, you believe me?

247
00:13:28,947 --> 00:13:31,039
- Everything's gonna be all
right, just relax, honey,

248
00:13:31,089 --> 00:13:32,360
just relax, please.

249
00:13:32,410 --> 00:13:34,454
Uh, thank you, sir, I'll take care of her.

250
00:13:34,504 --> 00:13:35,574
Come on, let's go.

251
00:13:35,624 --> 00:13:36,774
- Phil, he wants to kill me.

252
00:13:36,824 --> 00:13:37,633
- Sure.

253
00:13:37,683 --> 00:13:39,814
- Wait, you don't believe
me either, do you?

254
00:13:39,864 --> 00:13:41,898
- Gail, when are you gonna
start acting like a pro?

255
00:13:41,948 --> 00:13:43,201
You need to rest, come on.

256
00:13:43,251 --> 00:13:45,234
- Listen, you think I'm nuts.

257
00:13:45,284 --> 00:13:46,607
You do, don't deny it.

258
00:13:46,657 --> 00:13:48,189
- Of course I believe
you and I wanna help you,

259
00:13:48,239 --> 00:13:49,722
but first you've gotta
get hold of yourself.

