You sure ain't dressed for huntin' season.

528
00:26:04,635 --> 00:26:08,302
(slow tense rhythmic music)

529
00:26:09,667 --> 00:26:11,661
There's many things the Lord gives ya

530
00:26:11,711 --> 00:26:13,968
after he takes your eyesight.

531
00:26:14,018 --> 00:26:18,345
For one thing, he gives
ya more common sense.

532
00:26:18,395 --> 00:26:20,501
(chuckles)

533
00:26:20,551 --> 00:26:22,931
- How long you been livin'
around here, old man?

534
00:26:22,981 --> 00:26:25,924
- [Marion] Well, I was
born here in these swamps.

535
00:26:25,974 --> 00:26:27,942
I haven't left 'em since.

536
00:26:27,992 --> 00:26:30,412
- You've never been into a town or city?

537
00:26:30,462 --> 00:26:33,006
- [Marion] Never had need to, Lady.

538
00:26:33,056 --> 00:26:34,489
- Well, you wouldn't happen
to know if there's a phone

539
00:26:34,539 --> 00:26:36,039
around here, would ya?

540
00:26:36,089 --> 00:26:36,922
- Oh, no.

541
00:26:38,220 --> 00:26:41,297
I heard about them new phone things.

542
00:26:41,347 --> 00:26:42,368
You talk in one end,

543
00:26:42,418 --> 00:26:44,193
and someone hears ya out the other.

544
00:26:44,243 --> 00:26:47,158
No, I'd rather talk to a man face to face.

545
00:26:47,208 --> 00:26:50,126
- Well, I hate to see what'd
happen if you got sick.

546
00:26:50,176 --> 00:26:51,584
Anyway, you take care of yourself.

547
00:26:51,634 --> 00:26:54,384
It's nice talkin' to ya, old man.

548
00:26:55,845 --> 00:26:59,998
- Oh no, so we're back
on our hike to nowhere.

549
00:27:00,048 --> 00:27:01,927
- Master, Master, we
need your help, Master!

550
00:27:01,977 --> 00:27:03,464
We need your help!

551
00:27:03,514 --> 00:27:06,014
(tense music)

552
00:27:09,049 --> 00:27:10,429
We need your help, Master!

553
00:27:10,479 --> 00:27:13,076
Come on, please, please,
please, come on, please!

554
00:27:13,126 --> 00:27:15,168
Come on, come on!

555
00:27:15,218 --> 00:27:16,348
(tense music)

556
00:27:16,398 --> 00:27:18,791
- [Marion] Quiet, boy, quiet!

557
00:27:18,841 --> 00:27:21,314
- She fell into the creek
and was pulled under.

558
00:27:21,364 --> 00:27:22,663
Please, Marion.

559
00:27:22,713 --> 00:27:25,433
- Ah, I'm sorry, Mister, she's dead.

560
00:27:25,483 --> 00:27:26,815
- Please, Marion.

561
00:27:26,865 --> 00:27:29,085
It ain't her time yet, it just ain't.

562
00:27:29,135 --> 00:27:32,153
- All right, put her down, put her down.

563
00:27:32,203 --> 00:27:35,733
Let her body feel the
strength of Mother Earth.

564
00:27:35,783 --> 00:27:37,063
- [Maggie] The girl is dead.

565
00:27:37,113 --> 00:27:38,634
Don't prolong this man's misery.

566
00:27:38,684 --> 00:27:39,517
- Earth,

567
00:27:40,642 --> 00:27:41,475
air,

568
00:27:42,674 --> 00:27:45,018
spirits of the universe!

569
00:27:45,068 --> 00:27:47,901
Oh, Lord, bring the power unto me!

570
00:27:50,205 --> 00:27:52,705
(tense music)

571
00:27:57,968 --> 00:28:00,968
(pulsating ringing)

572
00:28:16,103 --> 00:28:19,009
(mystical music)

573
00:28:19,059 --> 00:28:20,476
- Baby!

574
00:28:20,526 --> 00:28:22,709
Baby, my little girl!

575
00:28:22,759 --> 00:28:24,842
(crying)

576
00:28:25,700 --> 00:28:26,950
My little girl.

577
00:28:28,433 --> 00:28:29,345
- You all right, old man?

578
00:28:29,395 --> 00:28:30,632
- Yeah.

579
00:28:30,682 --> 00:28:32,138
(crying)

580
00:28:32,188 --> 00:28:34,133
- This is not possible.

581
00:28:34,183 --> 00:28:37,100
(slow tense music)

582
00:28:42,830 --> 00:28:45,124
Hey, does he always get
so exhausted afterward?

583
00:28:45,174 --> 00:28:46,552
- No, people used to come for miles

584
00:28:46,602 --> 00:28:48,076
for the touch of healin'.

585
00:28:48,126 --> 00:28:49,069
Please, Master, eat.

586
00:28:49,119 --> 00:28:52,298
- [Marion] Not now, dear boy, not now.

587
00:28:52,348 --> 00:28:54,156
You better stay close.

588
00:28:54,206 --> 00:28:56,706
Your time will be comin' soon.

589
00:28:57,700 --> 00:28:58,483
- Eat, please.

590
00:28:58,533 --> 00:28:59,603
- Hey, Gus, you wouldn't happen to know

591
00:28:59,653 --> 00:29:01,117
of a phone around here, would you?

592
00:29:01,167 --> 00:29:02,434
- Phone, what's that?

593
00:29:02,484 --> 00:29:03,931
- I, I'm sorry, my friend.

594
00:29:03,981 --> 00:29:06,584
I know I'm not much of a host,

595
00:29:06,634 --> 00:29:08,943
but I do hope you enjoy this

596
00:29:08,993 --> 00:29:09,778
small meal.

597
00:29:09,828 --> 00:29:11,626
- Oh no, Marion, you
shouldn't, uh, really.

598
00:29:11,676 --> 00:29:13,258
- Looks good, uh, can I?

599
00:29:13,308 --> 00:29:15,375
- Oh, help yourself.

600
00:29:15,425 --> 00:29:16,258
- Shut up!

601
00:29:17,984 --> 00:29:22,581
Marion, that girl, she
was dead, and I saw that.

602
00:29:22,631 --> 00:29:27,058
I don't understand it,
but I saw it, Marion.

603
00:29:27,108 --> 00:29:28,191
She was dead.

604
00:29:31,373 --> 00:29:34,790
- Care for something to wet your whistle?

605
00:29:36,068 --> 00:29:39,039
Uh, don't, don't forget I'm blind, boy.

606
00:29:39,089 --> 00:29:41,048
Close the door.

607
00:29:41,098 --> 00:29:44,962
Mosquitoes are quite hungry,
especially for young blood.

608
00:29:45,012 --> 00:29:48,520
- I could go for a shot there, Marion.

609
00:29:48,570 --> 00:29:50,303
Thank you.
- How 'bout you, Maggie?

610
00:29:50,353 --> 00:29:52,033
- Oh, no thanks, Marion.

611
00:29:52,083 --> 00:29:54,937
You know, you could be a rich man.

612
00:29:54,987 --> 00:29:57,868
- Well, I'm doin' all I can, ma'am.

613
00:29:57,918 --> 00:29:59,451
To you, my friends.

614
00:29:59,501 --> 00:30:00,334
- Yeah.

615
00:30:02,122 --> 00:30:04,372
(coughing)

616
00:30:06,141 --> 00:30:08,583
What the hell is this, Marion?

617
00:30:08,633 --> 00:30:12,038
(slow tense music)

618
00:30:12,088 --> 00:30:15,520
- Marion, tell me how you do it.

619
00:30:15,570 --> 00:30:18,582
- Oh, it's simple, even you can make it.

620
00:30:18,632 --> 00:30:21,998
- No, Marion, what she's
talkin' about is how you did it,

621
00:30:22,048 --> 00:30:24,505
how you brought back
life to that little girl.

622
00:30:24,555 --> 00:30:26,638
- Oh, you mean the touch.

623
00:30:28,333 --> 00:30:31,500
Well, when I was a boy, about his age,

624
00:30:32,879 --> 00:30:35,265
the touch was passed on to me,

625
00:30:35,315 --> 00:30:37,982
just like I will pass it on to the boy.

626
00:30:38,032 --> 00:30:39,616
Right?

627
00:30:39,666 --> 00:30:43,083
Just like it's been done for 2,000 years.

628
00:30:44,578 --> 00:30:46,073
- It's time to go, Master.

629
00:30:46,123 --> 00:30:47,682
- Ah.

630
00:30:47,732 --> 00:30:51,479
- Little girl has really
tired me out tonight.

631
00:30:51,529 --> 00:30:53,828
- A lot of people have
travelled great distances

632
00:30:53,878 --> 00:30:55,058
to come here, Master.

633
00:30:55,108 --> 00:30:57,202
- Oh, you're right, boy.

634
00:30:57,252 --> 00:31:01,682
We mustn't disappoint those
who have been hoping so long.

635
00:31:01,732 --> 00:31:03,609
Come, friends.

636
00:31:03,659 --> 00:31:07,410
Come and witness the power of the touch.

637
00:31:07,460 --> 00:31:10,793
(gentle rhythmic music)

638
00:31:29,696 --> 00:31:31,979
A good evening to you all.

639
00:31:32,029 --> 00:31:36,040
(gentle rhythmic music)

640
00:31:36,090 --> 00:31:38,102
Thank you, boy.

641
00:31:38,152 --> 00:31:38,985
All right.

642
00:31:40,730 --> 00:31:44,563
I can see we got a load
of healin' work to do.

643
00:31:47,762 --> 00:31:48,595
Lord,

644
00:31:50,116 --> 00:31:52,949
we are here to heal your children.

645
00:31:53,932 --> 00:31:57,765
They hurt from the pain
of bein' mortal, Lord.

646
00:31:59,072 --> 00:32:02,969
Give me the power to take their pain away.

647
00:32:03,019 --> 00:32:05,608
Give me the power to heal.

648
00:32:05,658 --> 00:32:08,991
(gentle rhythmic music)

649
00:32:10,053 --> 00:32:11,636
Let the touch heal.

650
00:32:13,330 --> 00:32:16,663
(solemn rhythmic music)

651
00:32:36,846 --> 00:32:40,251
- This guy has gold in his hands, Bart.

652
00:32:40,301 --> 00:32:43,634
(solemn rhythmic music)

653
00:33:00,546 --> 00:33:01,713
(clattering)

654
00:33:01,763 --> 00:33:03,051
(chuckles)

655
00:33:03,101 --> 00:33:04,579
- This is impossible.

656
00:33:04,629 --> 00:33:05,703
- It's incredible.

657
00:33:05,753 --> 00:33:06,697
- Impossible.

658
00:33:06,747 --> 00:33:08,344
- It's incredible.

659
00:33:08,394 --> 00:33:12,561
(chuckles)
(solemn rhythmic music)

660
00:33:21,631 --> 00:33:23,810
- Come on, Maggie, let's
get a ride with one of them.

661
00:33:23,860 --> 00:33:25,755
- And miss this opportunity?

662
00:33:25,805 --> 00:33:27,888
We have to work this out.

663
00:33:29,680 --> 00:33:31,676
- Better stay close, boy.

664
00:33:31,726 --> 00:33:33,709
Your time will be comin' soon.

665
00:33:33,759 --> 00:33:35,579
- What exactly does that mean, Marion?

666
00:33:35,629 --> 00:33:37,241
His time will be comin' soon.

667
00:33:37,291 --> 00:33:41,224
- Well, my days are endin', my friends.

668
00:33:41,274 --> 00:33:45,441
Soon it will be my time to
pass the touch on to the boy,

669
00:33:46,674 --> 00:33:51,251
and he will have the power
to heal the many who need it.

670
00:33:51,301 --> 00:33:54,956
Come, let's go home and get some rest.

671
00:33:55,006 --> 00:33:57,048
- Um, the boy is much too young.

672
00:33:57,098 --> 00:33:59,365
I mean, don't you realize
what you have here?

673
00:33:59,415 --> 00:34:01,186
The millions that you can be makin'

674
00:34:01,236 --> 00:34:03,481
instead of wastin' your
time in these back swamps.

675
00:34:03,531 --> 00:34:04,827
- Yeah, she's right, Marion.

676
00:34:04,877 --> 00:34:06,783
This power you have, it's just incredible.

677
00:34:06,833 --> 00:34:08,842
We could set up some sort
of a clinic or somethin'.

678
00:34:08,892 --> 00:34:10,007
People would flock to this thing

679
00:34:10,057 --> 00:34:11,402
from all--
- Ah, no, no.

680
00:34:11,452 --> 00:34:14,492
- Marion, you gotta consider
how much you could help

681
00:34:14,542 --> 00:34:18,073
these poor people and we
can organize that for you.

682
00:34:18,123 --> 00:34:21,340
- You better get some rest yourselves.

683
00:34:21,390 --> 00:34:24,414
(slow rhythmic music)

684
00:34:24,464 --> 00:34:27,955
- Oh, honey, just think of
all the money we can make.

685
00:34:28,005 --> 00:34:29,494
- You're right, you're damn right.

686
00:34:29,544 --> 00:34:31,420
- We've just gotta make
him see it our way.

687
00:34:31,470 --> 00:34:35,700
Just think of it,
mansions, airplanes, limos.

688
00:34:35,750 --> 00:34:38,234
Oh, Bart, we just gotta get a limo!

689
00:34:38,284 --> 00:34:39,067
- Yeah.

690
00:34:39,117 --> 00:34:40,654
- Oh, yeah.

691
00:34:40,704 --> 00:34:43,871
(slow rhythmic music)

692
00:34:46,822 --> 00:34:48,719
(coughing)

693
00:34:48,769 --> 00:34:49,602
- Gus.

694
00:34:51,821 --> 00:34:52,654
Gus.

695
00:34:54,828 --> 00:34:55,661
Gus.

696
00:35:03,569 --> 00:35:05,515
- Don't worry, I'll take him into it.

697
00:35:05,565 --> 00:35:07,272
Some fresh squeezed orange juice

698
00:35:07,322 --> 00:35:08,420
and egg in the mornin',

699
00:35:08,470 --> 00:35:10,799
that's all it takes to gain a man.

700
00:35:10,849 --> 00:35:11,682
- Gus!

701
00:35:12,688 --> 00:35:14,302
(coughing)

702
00:35:14,352 --> 00:35:15,185
Gus!

703
00:35:16,722 --> 00:35:18,585
- [Bart] It's okay, Marion, we're here.

704
00:35:18,635 --> 00:35:19,795
- Oh, Gus!

705
00:35:19,845 --> 00:35:22,587
- [Maggie] I made ya
some fresh brewed coffee.

706
00:35:22,637 --> 00:35:23,804
- Oh, the boy,

707
00:35:24,830 --> 00:35:26,913
please, bring me the boy.

708
00:35:29,656 --> 00:35:32,209
- Bart, this is our chance.

709
00:35:32,259 --> 00:35:33,042
- Gus.

710
00:35:33,092 --> 00:35:35,052
- Just think what we
can do with this power,

711
00:35:35,102 --> 00:35:36,230
just do it.

712
00:35:36,280 --> 00:35:37,113
Come on.

713
00:35:40,078 --> 00:35:41,584
- [Bart] I don't know
where the boy is, Marion.

714
00:35:41,634 --> 00:35:42,442
What's wrong?

715
00:35:42,492 --> 00:35:45,000
- The boy, I need Gus.

716
00:35:45,050 --> 00:35:45,887
- [Bart] No, no, look,

717
00:35:45,937 --> 00:35:47,506
it's gonna be all right.
- Gus!

718
00:35:47,556 --> 00:35:49,401
- I'll go and get him.

719
00:35:49,451 --> 00:35:52,701
(tense rhythmic music)

720
00:35:53,753 --> 00:35:54,813
Gus!

721
00:35:54,863 --> 00:35:57,380
Gus, Marion needs ya!

722
00:35:57,430 --> 00:35:59,090
(tense rhythmic music)

723
00:35:59,140 --> 00:35:59,973
Gus!

724
00:36:01,719 --> 00:36:03,555
- Thanks for your help.

725
00:36:03,605 --> 00:36:05,103
You're good people.

726
00:36:05,153 --> 00:36:06,958
- You're welcome, old man.

727
00:36:07,008 --> 00:36:09,875
Listen, why don't ya
give that touch to me?

728
00:36:09,925 --> 00:36:11,972
Gus is much too young.

729
00:36:12,022 --> 00:36:13,134
Give the touch to me,

730
00:36:13,184 --> 00:36:16,064
old man.
- No, the boy must be the one.

731
00:36:16,114 --> 00:36:17,997
The touch must heal.

732
00:36:18,047 --> 00:36:21,297
(tense rhythmic music)

733
00:36:27,191 --> 00:36:28,175
- I don't see him.

734
00:36:28,225 --> 00:36:29,311
(Marion moans)

735
00:36:29,361 --> 00:36:30,706
I, I tripped.

736
00:36:30,756 --> 00:36:33,690
- The boy, I need the boy.

737
00:36:33,740 --> 00:36:35,384
- I will heal the sick, old man.

738
00:36:35,434 --> 00:36:37,741
I will help you out, give me the touch.

739
00:36:37,791 --> 00:36:39,186
- Swear.

740
00:36:39,236 --> 00:36:42,889
Swear it to me that you will
help the sick and the poor.

741
00:36:42,939 --> 00:36:46,022
- I swear it, old man, I swear it.

742
00:36:46,072 --> 00:36:48,447
I will help you out, give me the touch.

743
00:36:48,497 --> 00:36:51,747
(tense rhythmic music)

744
00:36:53,820 --> 00:36:54,820
- This gift,

745
00:36:56,313 --> 00:36:58,146
the gift of the touch,

746
00:36:59,580 --> 00:37:02,747
it shall pass from teacher to student.

747
00:37:03,724 --> 00:37:07,197
You shall pass it on when your time comes.

748
00:37:07,247 --> 00:37:09,486
Swear to me that it shall be done.

749
00:37:09,536 --> 00:37:11,944
- No, let go of my hands, they're burning!

750
00:37:11,994 --> 00:37:13,580
- Swear it to me!

751
00:37:13,630 --> 00:37:15,375
- Swear it, damn it!

752
00:37:15,425 --> 00:37:17,869
- Oh, God, I swear it!

753
00:37:17,919 --> 00:37:19,800
(tense music)

754
00:37:19,850 --> 00:37:20,662
- You got it!

755
00:37:20,712 --> 00:37:21,495
You okay?

756
00:37:21,545 --> 00:37:23,295
- They're burning, they're burning.

757
00:37:23,345 --> 00:37:24,718
- It hurts.

758
00:37:24,768 --> 00:37:26,200
(tense music)

759
00:37:26,250 --> 00:37:27,033
We did it!

760
00:37:27,083 --> 00:37:29,333
We did it, we did it, whoa!

761
00:37:30,780 --> 00:37:33,735
We did it, come on, come
on, let's get outta here!

762
00:37:33,785 --> 00:37:37,035
(tense rhythmic music)

763
00:37:47,746 --> 00:37:49,924
- I don't have time for this nonsense.

764
00:37:49,974 --> 00:37:50,757
- Sit down.

765
00:37:50,807 --> 00:37:52,124
Ramsey screen it.

766
00:37:52,174 --> 00:37:54,674
It's supposed to be fantastic.

767
00:38:00,657 --> 00:38:02,952
- All right, um, why don't
you two just have a seat?

768
00:38:03,002 --> 00:38:04,820
I'll be right with you, okay?

769
00:38:04,870 --> 00:38:06,289
Now, don't you worry.

770
00:38:06,339 --> 00:38:09,702
Everything's gonna be okay, all right?

771
00:38:09,752 --> 00:38:12,468
Gentlemen, what I am about to show you

772
00:38:12,518 --> 00:38:15,962
is, by no other explanation, a miracle.

773
00:38:16,012 --> 00:38:17,393
(chuckles)

774
00:38:17,443 --> 00:38:20,391
- Dr. Ramsey, with all due respect, sir,

775
00:38:20,441 --> 00:38:23,115
we do not believe in miracles.

776
00:38:23,165 --> 00:38:25,332
- Gentlemen, wait and see.

777
00:38:26,932 --> 00:38:29,949
This patient has been
diagnosed with terminal cancer.

778
00:38:29,999 --> 00:38:32,689
The primary mass is formed in the colon.

779
00:38:32,739 --> 00:38:34,475
His kidneys are failing.

780
00:38:34,525 --> 00:38:37,169
Further medical intervention
is out of the question,

781
00:38:37,219 --> 00:38:39,085
except to make his short time left

782
00:38:39,135 --> 00:38:41,494
as comfortable as possible.

783
00:38:41,544 --> 00:38:43,377
Mr. Carlin, you ready?

784
00:38:46,365 --> 00:38:48,615
Nurse, the curtain, please.

785
00:38:49,807 --> 00:38:53,370
Nurse, could you close the
curtain, please, quickly?

786
00:38:53,420 --> 00:38:55,689
Gentlemen, this is Mr. Bart Carlin.

787
00:38:55,739 --> 00:38:57,624
He is going to attempt a miracle.

788
00:38:57,674 --> 00:38:59,880
He is going to cure the patient.

789
00:38:59,930 --> 00:39:03,180
(tense rhythmic music)

790
00:39:28,915 --> 00:39:31,665
(mystical music)

791
00:39:32,982 --> 00:39:33,853
Thank you, Bart.

792
00:39:33,903 --> 00:39:36,375
Could you have a seat, please?

793
00:39:36,425 --> 00:39:37,692
(tense rhythmic music)

794
00:39:37,742 --> 00:39:39,575
- So, how do you feel?

795
00:39:40,415 --> 00:39:42,915
- Better, I never felt better.

796
00:39:44,788 --> 00:39:47,068
- His records can be verified, of course.

797
00:39:47,118 --> 00:39:50,098
- [Doctor] I would like to
see a complete lab analysis.

798
00:39:50,148 --> 00:39:51,632
- Of course.

799
00:39:51,682 --> 00:39:53,701
- This is amazing, Doctor.

800
00:39:53,751 --> 00:39:55,514
I would've sworn that
this patient suffered from

801
00:39:55,564 --> 00:39:57,055
poor blood circulation.

802
00:39:57,105 --> 00:40:00,758
- [Dr. Ramsey] He did, over
60% his arteries were clogged.

803
00:40:00,808 --> 00:40:03,180
- Did you see the color of his skin?

804
00:40:03,230 --> 00:40:04,696
It's impossible.

805
00:40:04,746 --> 00:40:07,076
- Ah, that's what makes it most exciting.

806
00:40:07,126 --> 00:40:10,895
By all rights, this man
was a walking corpse.

807
00:40:10,945 --> 00:40:14,195
(tense rhythmic music)

808
00:40:17,660 --> 00:40:20,493
(soft chattering)

809
00:40:22,822 --> 00:40:25,072
(knocking)

810
00:40:28,487 --> 00:40:29,420
- We quit!

811
00:40:29,470 --> 00:40:31,588
(chuckles)

812
00:40:31,638 --> 00:40:33,433
- What, what's going on here?

813
00:40:33,483 --> 00:40:35,167
- Well, it's like this, Dr. Ramsey.

814
00:40:35,217 --> 00:40:37,650
I've been working for you
and this medical institution

815
00:40:37,700 --> 00:40:39,194
for what, two months now?

816
00:40:39,244 --> 00:40:41,661
And everyone of the
patients that I've cured

817
00:40:41,711 --> 00:40:44,168
have been probed and
studied by your doctors.

818
00:40:44,218 --> 00:40:46,735
Now, cured is the key word here, Ramsey.

819
00:40:46,785 --> 00:40:48,293
- Look at all this crap.

820
00:40:48,343 --> 00:40:50,925
None of these fancy degrees
can do what Bart can do

821
00:40:50,975 --> 00:40:52,718
with just his touch.

822
00:40:52,768 --> 00:40:55,969
- No, I don't have that gift
of healing that you have.

823
00:40:56,019 --> 00:40:58,850
- Ha, you can't even
call yourself a healer.

824
00:40:58,900 --> 00:41:00,861
Not when I'm in the same room.

825
00:41:00,911 --> 00:41:03,797
- Sure, every AIDS and cancer
patient in our hospital

826
00:41:03,847 --> 00:41:05,390
is cured by your hands.

827
00:41:05,440 --> 00:41:07,209
Your gift is doing lots of good here.

828
00:41:07,259 --> 00:41:10,464
- Exactly, I've been healin'
a lot of people in this place

829
00:41:10,514 --> 00:41:11,538
for a long time.

830
00:41:11,588 --> 00:41:13,154
Where has it gotten me?

831
00:41:13,204 --> 00:41:14,303
- You've been paid.

832
00:41:14,353 --> 00:41:16,055
You've been paid very well.

833
00:41:16,105 --> 00:41:18,193
- Paid well, Ramsey?

834
00:41:18,243 --> 00:41:20,909
And who's gettin' the big bucks here, huh?

835
00:41:20,959 --> 00:41:23,217
- All right, how much do ya want?

836
00:41:23,267 --> 00:41:26,234
(chuckles)

837
00:41:26,284 --> 00:41:29,089
- You ever heard of the
Medical Corporation?

838
00:41:29,139 --> 00:41:31,693
- [Dr. Ramsey] Yes, they
own hospitals and clinics,

839
00:41:31,743 --> 00:41:34,261
a sort of General Motors in hospital care.

840
00:41:34,311 --> 00:41:37,304
- They've offered us six
million, excluding benefits,

841
00:41:37,354 --> 00:41:40,509
excluding bonuses, plus our own clinic.

842
00:41:40,559 --> 00:41:42,807
Can you beat that?

843
00:41:42,857 --> 00:41:45,271
The Bart Carlin Clinic.

844
00:41:45,321 --> 00:41:47,490
I like the sound of that.

845
00:41:47,540 --> 00:41:49,373
- So do I, so we quit.

846
00:41:50,807 --> 00:41:53,545
Unless of course you can
make us a better offer.

847
00:41:53,595 --> 00:41:55,595
- You have a great gift.

848
00:41:56,489 --> 00:41:57,920
Don't whore it.

849
00:41:57,970 --> 00:42:00,504
- Oh (sighs).

850
00:42:00,554 --> 00:42:02,971
(door thuds)

851
00:42:11,565 --> 00:42:14,398
(soft chattering)

852
00:42:25,442 --> 00:42:26,762
- [Man] As chairman of the board

853
00:42:26,812 --> 00:42:28,658
for the Medical Corporation,

854
00:42:28,708 --> 00:42:33,109
I personally wish to
congratulate Mr. Bart Carlin.

855
00:42:33,159 --> 00:42:35,818
It is my pleasure to declare
the Bart Carlin Clinic

856
00:42:35,868 --> 00:42:37,501
officially open.

857
00:42:37,551 --> 00:42:38,446
Bart.

858
00:42:38,496 --> 00:42:40,746
(clapping)

859
00:42:45,890 --> 00:42:50,057
- Today marks the beginning of
a new era in world medicine.

860
00:42:51,114 --> 00:42:53,856
The Bart Carlin Clinic will change

861
00:42:53,906 --> 00:42:56,416
the medical world forever.

862
00:42:56,466 --> 00:42:57,923
Get 'em rollin', Maggie!

863
00:42:57,973 --> 00:42:59,516
- All right, cash to the left,

864
00:42:59,566 --> 00:43:01,372
insurance and credit cards to the right.

865
00:43:01,422 --> 00:43:04,939
And remember, please
fill out the proper form.

866
00:43:04,989 --> 00:43:08,572
(easygoing rhythmic music)

867
00:43:11,127 --> 00:43:13,245
- High blood pressure, diabetes, and, uh,

868
00:43:13,295 --> 00:43:14,864
cancer of the liver.

869
00:43:14,914 --> 00:43:18,073
This is an interesting start.

870
00:43:18,123 --> 00:43:19,676
- Yeah, cash or credit?

871
00:43:19,726 --> 00:43:21,393
- Cash, 3,000 bucks.

872
00:43:22,480 --> 00:43:23,866
- 3,000 bucks.

873
00:43:23,916 --> 00:43:26,311
Well, for 3,000 bucks we can
take care of the diabetes

874
00:43:26,361 --> 00:43:28,303
and the blood pressure, but the cancer,

875
00:43:28,353 --> 00:43:29,799
nah, I don't think so.

876
00:43:29,849 --> 00:43:31,312
- [Maggie] I think you're right.

877
00:43:31,362 --> 00:43:33,742
- [Patient] Please, I'll
give you anything, anything,

878
00:43:33,792 --> 00:43:34,875
just help me.

879
00:43:36,284 --> 00:43:37,940
- Maggie, sweetie,

880
00:43:37,990 --> 00:43:39,953
bring this gentleman
the standard $8,000 note

881
00:43:40,003 --> 00:43:42,444
and let him sign that, please.

882
00:43:42,494 --> 00:43:45,661
(soft rhythmic music)

883
00:43:52,784 --> 00:43:53,667
Off we go.

884
00:43:53,717 --> 00:43:55,793
(claps)

885
00:43:55,843 --> 00:43:59,010
(soft rhythmic music)

886
00:44:06,045 --> 00:44:08,023
Hey, it's funny, I.

887
00:44:08,073 --> 00:44:10,789
- Stop it, it burns, stop it!

888
00:44:10,839 --> 00:44:11,975
Stop!

889
00:44:12,025 --> 00:44:12,858
Stop!

890
00:44:14,143 --> 00:44:16,578
(yells)
(dramatic music)

891
00:44:16,628 --> 00:44:17,968
- What is goin' on here?

892
00:44:18,018 --> 00:44:19,379
- This isn't supposed to happen.

893
00:44:19,429 --> 00:44:20,262
This, uh,

894
00:44:21,986 --> 00:44:23,099
next!

895
00:44:23,149 --> 00:44:25,002
- Come on, next, please.

896
00:44:25,052 --> 00:44:26,828
- This can't be.

897
00:44:26,878 --> 00:44:28,158
This can't be.

898
00:44:28,208 --> 00:44:29,676
(tense music)

899
00:44:29,726 --> 00:44:32,413
Uh, this isn't supposed to happen.

900
00:44:32,463 --> 00:44:33,246
Next!

901
00:44:33,296 --> 00:44:35,802
(yells)

902
00:44:35,852 --> 00:44:38,147
(screams)

903
00:44:38,197 --> 00:44:40,654
(tense music)

904
00:44:40,704 --> 00:44:43,276
(screaming)

905
00:44:43,326 --> 00:44:44,940
I'm supposed to heal!

906
00:44:44,990 --> 00:44:46,293
- Stop it!

907
00:44:46,343 --> 00:44:48,676
- No, it's supposed to heal!

908
00:44:50,849 --> 00:44:52,161
Maggie!

909
00:44:52,211 --> 00:44:53,375
- No!

910
00:44:53,425 --> 00:44:57,592
(screams)
(tense music)

911
00:45:02,250 --> 00:45:03,083
- Maggie.

912
00:45:08,521 --> 00:45:11,594
- The most unique thing
of all is that the boy

913
00:45:11,644 --> 00:45:15,662
somehow or other can
perform what has to be

914
00:45:15,712 --> 00:45:17,462
the power of healing.

915
00:45:21,538 --> 00:45:24,288
- Oh, I'm glad they let you come.

916
00:45:25,939 --> 00:45:27,856
You know why don't you?

917
00:45:31,325 --> 00:45:35,204
The touch was always meant to be yours.

918
00:45:35,254 --> 00:45:37,951
I cheated you out of your gift.

919
00:45:38,001 --> 00:45:42,168
(groans)
(tense rhythmic music)

920
00:45:49,435 --> 00:45:50,268
Now,

921
00:45:52,459 --> 00:45:54,195
it is yours.

922
00:45:54,245 --> 00:45:57,495
(tense rhythmic music)

923
00:46:01,632 --> 00:46:03,536
- Did he dream it?

924
00:46:03,586 --> 00:46:05,847
Or did he actually live it?

925
00:46:05,897 --> 00:46:08,897
I don't know whether to question it or

926
00:46:08,947 --> 00:46:10,364
let him continue.

927
00:46:11,995 --> 00:46:13,825
The miracles that the boy performed,

928
00:46:13,875 --> 00:46:17,792
somehow that seems to
outweigh everything else.

929
00:46:18,820 --> 00:46:22,070
(tense rhythmic music)

930
00:46:43,459 --> 00:46:45,168
- [Man] I need to talk about this.

931
00:46:45,218 --> 00:46:47,444
I found myself having some dreams.

932
00:46:47,494 --> 00:46:49,434
- Tell me about 'em.

933
00:46:49,484 --> 00:46:52,401
(slow tense music)

934
00:46:59,383 --> 00:47:01,550
(beeping)

935
00:47:09,854 --> 00:47:13,034
(doors swoosh)

936
00:47:13,084 --> 00:47:16,001
(slow tense music)

937
00:47:34,900 --> 00:47:37,233
(swooshing)

938
00:47:38,469 --> 00:47:40,636
(beeping)

939
00:47:51,043 --> 00:47:52,560
- Good morning, Bud.

940
00:47:52,610 --> 00:47:54,694
- Good morning, McCarthy.

941
00:47:54,744 --> 00:47:56,080
Any news?

942
00:47:56,130 --> 00:47:58,297
(beeping)

943
00:48:00,466 --> 00:48:02,443
- [McCarthy] My last transmission received

944
00:48:02,493 --> 00:48:06,660
showed that the Miami Heat
finally won NBA Championship.

945
00:48:08,842 --> 00:48:12,764
However, due to our distance from Earth,

946
00:48:12,814 --> 00:48:15,206
that news is 14 years old.

947
00:48:15,256 --> 00:48:18,329
(beeping)
(tense music)

948
00:48:18,379 --> 00:48:19,712
Coffee is ready.

949
00:48:20,648 --> 00:48:24,815
(beeping)
(tense music)

950
00:48:35,877 --> 00:48:40,396
- You know, I never
would've bet on them anyway.

951
00:48:40,446 --> 00:48:43,113
(door swooshes)

952
00:48:43,976 --> 00:48:47,643
(upbeat instrumental music)

953
00:48:50,512 --> 00:48:53,512
- Bud, may I ask you some questions?

954
00:48:54,764 --> 00:48:57,471
- [Bud] Are these for the psych reports?

955
00:48:57,521 --> 00:48:59,487
- I know they're bothersome.

956
00:48:59,537 --> 00:49:00,365
- Shoot.

957
00:49:00,415 --> 00:49:02,787
- [McCarthy] How do you
feel about being so far away

958
00:49:02,837 --> 00:49:04,582
from another human being?

959
00:49:04,632 --> 00:49:08,550
- Well, it doesn't really
feel like it's been that long.

960
00:49:08,600 --> 00:49:10,978
You know, with the suspended animation,

961
00:49:11,028 --> 00:49:12,947
it feels like it's been
just a couple of weeks.

962
00:49:12,997 --> 00:49:14,850
- That's the way it's supposed to feel.

963
00:49:14,900 --> 00:49:17,249
Do you ever wonder what
the others will be like?

964
00:49:17,299 --> 00:49:18,623
- What, the new planet?

965
00:49:18,673 --> 00:49:21,599
- Yes, after all, you
will be the first earthman

966
00:49:21,649 --> 00:49:24,581
to set foot on a known habitat planet.

967
00:49:24,631 --> 00:49:26,541
- A new Columbus, huh?

968
00:49:26,591 --> 00:49:28,943
The only problem is it
takes about a 100 years

969
00:49:28,993 --> 00:49:31,013
to go back and forth.

970
00:49:31,063 --> 00:49:32,675
By the time my findings reach Earth,

971
00:49:32,725 --> 00:49:35,680
everything and everybody
I know will be history.

972
00:49:35,730 --> 00:49:37,412
- Are you still dreaming?

973
00:49:37,462 --> 00:49:39,444
- Well, there's some question
about that back on Earth.

974
00:49:39,494 --> 00:49:41,965
- [McCarthy] Yes, I
remember the discussion.

975
00:49:42,015 --> 00:49:44,465
It was believed that if
your mind was very active

976
00:49:44,515 --> 00:49:46,203
during the sleep stage,

977
00:49:46,253 --> 00:49:48,286
it might age faster than the body.

978
00:49:48,336 --> 00:49:50,228
- Yeah, well, what's actually happening

979
00:49:50,278 --> 00:49:52,604
is my dreams are being stretched out.

980
00:49:52,654 --> 00:49:55,674
Instead of having 300 dreams a year,

981
00:49:55,724 --> 00:49:57,724
I'm having one long one.

982
00:49:59,750 --> 00:50:02,545
(beeping)

983
00:50:02,595 --> 00:50:06,012
- Bud, may I ask you a personal question?

984
00:50:07,006 --> 00:50:08,331
- Shoot.

985
00:50:08,381 --> 00:50:10,836
- What is it like to dream?

986
00:50:10,886 --> 00:50:13,136
(chuckles)

987
00:50:20,251 --> 00:50:22,584
(swooshing)

988
00:50:27,178 --> 00:50:29,180
- Well, goodnight, McCarthy.

989
00:50:29,230 --> 00:50:31,855
See ya in about a year.

990
00:50:31,905 --> 00:50:34,072
(beeping)

991
00:50:39,931 --> 00:50:42,514
(doors swoosh)

992
00:50:44,296 --> 00:50:46,879
(machine hums)

993
00:50:49,886 --> 00:50:52,386
(heart beats)

994
00:50:56,504 --> 00:51:00,671
(gentle instrumental music)
(animals chirp)

995
00:51:16,424 --> 00:51:18,007
- [Woman] Bud, Bud!

996
00:51:19,193 --> 00:51:20,759
- Hey, Mom!

997
00:51:20,809 --> 00:51:23,392
(gentle music)

998
00:51:28,148 --> 00:51:29,444
- Come on in, Bud.

999
00:51:29,494 --> 00:51:31,784
I'm making you breakfast.

1000
00:51:31,834 --> 00:51:34,808
(animals chirp)

1001
00:51:34,858 --> 00:51:37,191
(swooshing)

1002
00:51:39,377 --> 00:51:40,710
Bud, come on in.

1003
00:51:41,777 --> 00:51:43,444
Bud, get on in here.

1004
00:51:45,322 --> 00:51:49,489
(gentle music)
(chirping)

1005
00:51:51,241 --> 00:51:52,827
- Mom.

1006
00:51:52,877 --> 00:51:57,044
(growling)
(dramatic music)

1007
00:52:15,843 --> 00:52:17,593
- Welcome, Commander.

1008
00:52:19,020 --> 00:52:21,756
(gentle music)
(animals chirp)

1009
00:52:21,806 --> 00:52:24,164
We knew you would come.

1010
00:52:24,214 --> 00:52:28,381
(gentle music)
(animals chirp)

1011
00:52:42,203 --> 00:52:44,203
- You look just like us.

1012
00:52:46,766 --> 00:52:49,214
- Yes, we are sort of just like you.

1013
00:52:49,264 --> 00:52:51,263
- You said sort of, what do you mean?

1014
00:52:51,313 --> 00:52:54,896
- We're alike in many
ways, except for one.

1015
00:52:56,216 --> 00:52:57,383
- What's that?

1016
00:52:59,862 --> 00:53:01,294
- We eat human.

1017
00:53:01,344 --> 00:53:03,414
(clattering)

1018
00:53:03,464 --> 00:53:05,964
(tense music)

1019
00:53:07,503 --> 00:53:08,286
(beeping)

1020
00:53:08,336 --> 00:53:11,169
(McCarthy buzzes)

1021
00:53:17,275 --> 00:53:20,078
- You seem perturbed about something, Bud.

1022
00:53:20,128 --> 00:53:22,705
- McCarthy, you better turn
on your psych recording.

1023
00:53:22,755 --> 00:53:24,621
I need to talk about this.

1024
00:53:24,671 --> 00:53:26,103
- [McCarthy] Go ahead.

1025
00:53:26,153 --> 00:53:29,502
- You know, the last few times
I've been in the SA stage,

1026
00:53:29,552 --> 00:53:32,300
I found myself having
some pretty weird dreams.

1027
00:53:32,350 --> 00:53:35,543
I'm being chased by some
very bizarre critters.

1028
00:53:35,593 --> 00:53:37,759
- I've analysed what you've told me so far

1029
00:53:37,809 --> 00:53:39,083
with my psych tapes.

